    <briefdescription>
<para>Optimal-speed rate conversion cascade. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Selects the cheapest cascade of CIC, HalfbandDecimator, and/or polyphase Resampler stages for a given output/input sample rate ratio at creation time. All sub-stage C objects are owned by the state struct.</para>
<para>Stage selection (D = 1/rate):</para>
<para>rate &gt;= 1.0 or D &lt; 2 [Resampler(rate)] D ~= 2^1 [HalfbandDecimator] D ~= 2^2 [HalfbandDecimator, HalfbandDecimator] D ~= 2^n, n&gt;=3, D&lt;=4096 [CIC(D)] D &gt;= 8, non-power-of-2 [CIC(R*), Resampler correction] R* = nearest power-of-2 to D otherwise (2 &lt;= D &lt; 8, non-int) [Resampler(rate)]</para>
